<h2><a name="length" id="length">length</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Syntax:
</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;string&gt;</span>
    size_type length<span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="br0">&#41;</span> <span class="kw4">const</span>;</pre>
<p>

The length() function returns the number of elements in the current string,
performing the same role as the size() function.
</p>

<p>
If testing whether a string is empty or not, use empty() since it doesn&#039;t need to count beyond the first character in the string.
</p>

<p>
Related Topics: <a href="capacity" class="wikilink1" title="string:capacity">capacity</a>, <a href="empty" class="wikilink1" title="string:empty">empty</a>, <a href="max_size" class="wikilink1" title="string:max_size">max_size</a>, <a href="resize" class="wikilink1" title="string:resize">resize</a>, <a href="size" class="wikilink1" title="string:size">size</a>
</p>

</div>
